HEADWORD: Channeling
<hw>Chan"nel*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process
of forming a channel or channels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A channel or a system of channels; a
groove.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chanson</ent>⟦br⟧
